A three-storey building under construction collapsed in the Yaba area of Lagos State, on Saturday. The building is located on Akanbi Crescent, near the main gate of University of Lagos, UNILAG. It collapsed onto a building beside it on Saturday afternoon. More details of the collapsed building were sketchy as at the time of filing this report. However, several construction workers in the area are said to be trapped in the rubbles. The Director General, Lagos State Emergency Management Agency (LASEMA), Dr. Olufemi Oke-Osanyintolu has confirmed the incident. Recall that a 21-storey Ikoyi building had collapsed last November in Lagos Femi Osibona, owner of Fourscore Homes, was one of the 43 persons who died in the collapse on November 1, 2021.